---
import HeroLayout from "../layouts/HeroLayout.astro"
---

<HeroLayout
  title="Hero Layout Test"
  description="Testing our new semantic hero layout with flexible content support"
>
  <div slot="hero-content">
    <button>Call to Action</button>
    <p>This is additional hero content that wasn't possible with hgroup!</p>
  </div>

  <article>
    <h2>Main Content</h2>
    <p>
      This content appears below the hero section, demonstrating that our hero
      layout properly integrates with the rest of the page structure.
    </p>

    <h3>Key Improvements</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>
        ✅ Semantic <code>&lt;header&gt;</code> element instead of <code
          >&lt;hgroup&gt;</code
        >
      </li>
      <li>✅ Flexible content support via slots</li>
      <li>✅ Simplified full-width background (no viewport width tricks)</li>
      <li>✅ Natural sticky integration for shadow removal</li>
      <li>✅ CSS custom property for header height</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Technical Details</h3>
    <p>
      The hero section now uses <code>main &gt; header</code> selector, which is:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>More semantic than <code>hgroup</code></li>
      <li>Completely classless - no need for additional classes</li>
      <li>Better integrated with navigation state management</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</HeroLayout>
